PrecisAmendments to the OZONE-DEPLETING SUBSTANCES REGULATIONS which are designed to implement the freeze on the consumption of METHYL BROMIDE at 1991 levels by the year 1995, as well as the additional Canadian commitment to reduce its consumption to 75% of the 1991 level by the year 1998.
